Integer\"><code>Number.isSafeInteger()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/parseFloat\"><code>Number.parseFloat()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/parseInt\"><code>Number.parseInt()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toExponential\"><code>Number.prototype.toExponential()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toFixed\"><code>Number.prototype.toFixed()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toLocaleString\"><code>Number.prototype.toLocaleString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toPrecision\"><code>Number.prototype.toPrecision()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toString\"><code>Number.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/valueOf\"><code>Number.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li><li><strong>Vererbung:</strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function\"><code>Function</code></a></strong></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Eigenschaften</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/arguments\"><code>Function.prototype.arguments</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/caller\"><code>Function.prototype.caller</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-nonstandard\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-nonstandard\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/displayName\"><code>Function.prototype.displayName</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/length\"><code>Function.prototype.length</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/name\"><code>Function.prototype.name</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/prototype\"><code>Function.prototype.prototype</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/apply\"><code>Function.prototype.apply()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/bind\"><code>Function.prototype.bind()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/call\"><code>Function.prototype.call()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/toString\"><code>Function.prototype.toString()</code></a></li></ol></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a></strong></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Eigenschaften</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/constructor\"><code>Object.prototype.constructor</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/proto\"><code>Object.prototype.__proto__</code></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Die <strong><code>Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code></strong> Eigenschaft repräsentiert den Wert der negativen Unendlichkeit.</p>\n\n<div id=\"sect2\"><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/number-negative-infinity.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Man muss kein Objekt vom Typ <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a> erzeugen, um Zugriff zu haben, weil diese Eigenschaft statisch ist (nutze&nbsp; <code>Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code>).</p>\n\n<div id=\"sect3\"><table class=\"standard-table\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th class=\"header\" colspan=\"2\">Eigenschaftsattribute von <code>Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code></th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Schreibbar</td>\n      <td>nein</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Aufzählbar</td>\n      <td>nein</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Konfigurierbar</td>\n      <td>nein</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"description","title":"Beschreibung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Der Wert von <code>Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> ist der gleiche wie der negative Wert der Eigenschaft <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Infinity\"><code>Infinity</code></a> des <em>globalen Objektes</em>.</p>\n\n<p>Der Wert verhält sich leicht unterschiedlich zu der mathematischen Unendlichkeit:</p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Jeder positive Wert, auch <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/POSITIVE_INFINITY\"><code>POSITIVE_INFINITY</code></a>, multipliziert mit <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> ergibt <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code>.</li>\n <li>Jeder negative Wert, auch <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code>, multipliziert mit&nbsp; <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> ergibt <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/POSITIVE_INFINITY\"><code>POSITIVE_INFINITY</code></a>.</li>\n <li>Jeder positive Wert dividiert durch <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> ergibt 0.</li>\n <li>Jeder negative Wert dividiert durch <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> ergibt 0.</li>\n <li>0 multipliziert mit <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> ergibt <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>.</li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> multipliziert mit <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> ergibt <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>.</li>\n <li><code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> dividiert durch jeden negativen Wert, mit Ausnahme <code>von NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code>, ergibt <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/POSITIVE_INFINITY\"><code>POSITIVE_INFINITY</code></a>.</li>\n <li><code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> dividiert durch jeden positiven Wert, mit Ausnahme von <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/POSITIVE_INFINITY\"><code>POSITIVE_INFINITY</code></a>, ergibt <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code>.</li>\n <li><code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> dividiert durch <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> oder <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/POSITIVE_INFINITY\"><code>POSITIVE_INFINITY</code></a> ergibt <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Man kann <code>Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code> nutzen, um einen Fehlerfall zu signalisieren, wenn im Normalfall ein endliches Ergebnis erwartet werden kann. Zudem kann ein Wert mit <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/isFinite\"><code>isFinite</code></a> auf seine <span class=\"dpf_sent\" id=\"dpfsent_4\">Endlichkeit </span>geprüft werden.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"einsatz_von_negative_infinity","title":"Einsatz von <code>NEGATIVE_INFINITY</code>","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Im folgenden Beispiel wird der Variablen<code> smallNumber</code> ein kleinerer Wert als der minimale Wert zugewiesen. Wenn das <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/if...else\"><code>if</code></a>-Statement ausgeführt wird, hat <code>smallNumber</code> den Wert <code>-Infinity</code>. In diesem Fall wird der Variablen ein endlicher Wert zugewiesen, um mit dem Wert besser umgehen zu können.</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> smallNumber <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span>Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token constant\">MAX_VALUE</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>smallNumber <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> Number<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token constant\">NEGATIVE_INFINITY</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  smallNumber <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">returnFinite</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Einsatz von NEGATIVE_INFINITY"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"spezifikationen","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST-ARCH/ECMA-262,%201st%20edition,%20June%201997.pdf\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"Die 'ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)' Spezifikation\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)</a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition. Implementiert in JavaScript 1.1.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/5.1/#sec-15.7.3.5\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 5.1 (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-number.negative_infinity\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-number.negative_infinity\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/NEGATIVE_INFINITY/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/POSITIVE_INFINITY\"><code>Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/isFinite\"><code>Number.isFinite()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Infinity\"><code>Infinity</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/isFinite\"><code>isFinite()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Beschreibung","id":"description"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"examples"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"spezifikationen"},{"text":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Die Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY Eigenschaft repräsentiert den Wert der negativen Unendlichkeit.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY","locale":"ko","na